Explore what’s next for the Cleveland metro as Valor Acres defines what it means to live, work, and enjoy with its ambitious mixed-use model set to reposition the market’s commercial center of gravity.

It will feature over 150,000 square feet of retail and restaurant space, which includes a freestanding grocery store, an upscale boutique hotel, and the Canvas, a luxury apartment community with 200+ units. The 660,000-square-foot Sherwin Williams Research and Development Center Headquarters is planned to open in mid-2024 and will bring over 900 employees. The project is led by Ohio-based DiGeronimo Companies. Although Cleveland is the second-largest metropolitan area in Ohio with over two million residents, destinations that embrace the modern consumer’s demand for a mixed-use hub have not been as plentiful as other major markets throughout the country. Get on the cutting edge of market trends and take advantage of this trailblazing opportunity by reserving a presence in Valor Acres today. Reach out now to learn more.

Name: Independence Technology Center
HIGHLIGHTS:
Strategic Location: Located in the most central commercial real estate submarket in Northeast Ohio, 2 miles to I-77 offering convenient accessibility.
Scalability and Expansion Opportunities: 500 - 229,000 SF available (space easily subdivided) is perfect for biotech, lab, data, or call center.
Environmental Sustainability & Data Center Tax Exemption: ITC incorporates a rooftop solar panel farm, geothermal HVAC system. LEED certified, Silver.


Robust Infrastructure: 10 MW of power with diverse utility feeds. A strong fiber ring with millisecond latency and data speed up to 100 Gb/s.
Advanced Security Measures: Fire protection, a sprinkler system, backup generators, advanced cooling systems, scalable network connectivity options.
Amenity Rich: Direct access to a running/bike trail, 1,800 free parking spaces, 38 restaurants & 5 childcare facilities within 5 to 7 minutes.
PROPERTY OVERVIEW:
Come home to one of Cleveland’s most well-connected modern office and industrial properties at the beautiful Independence Technology Center, a unique place to work alongside nature. 
   
•  Strategic Location:  
o	Located in the most central commercial real estate submarket in Northeast Ohio, ITC is a state-of-the-art 306,000-square-foot building with 3 loading dock bays and is located on a sprawling 40-acre campus.  
o	This property offers unparalleled opportunities for data center operations seeking a strategic and high-performance location.  The property is zoned both commercial and U-5 – Industrial (NEC).  
o	Extremely private and abuts the Metroparks, ITC is within 2 miles of I-77 and offers convenient access to major highways, airports, and public transportation. 
o	 ITC offers potential carrier hotel connectivity as the US East Coast connects to the Midwest through Cleveland.  
o	Cleveland, Ohio, is a top US cloud hub disaster recovery location. ITC offers low latency to Ashburn, Chicago, Detroit, Philadelphia, and NYC.  
o	60% of the US population lives within 600 miles of Ohio.  
o	Cleveland, Ohio is one of the lowest overall exposures to natural disaster risks in the Eastern US. 
  
•  Robust Infrastructure:  
o	Renovated in 2012 for the Cleveland Clinic Foundation, the additions and renovations were built and designed to meet first-class standards that can meet the needs of a data center. It features redundant power sources, backup generators, advanced cooling systems, and scalable network connectivity options to ensure continuous and reliable operations. 
o	The power grid serving ITC is one of the country’s most reliable and affordable, and ITC has the ability to provide 10 MW of power with diverse utility feeds. 
o	ITC can offer a robust fiber ring that provides millisecond latency. Fiber optic infrastructure in place from Everstream’s broadband network, which allows businesses to operate a converged IP network capable of delivering strong voice, video, and data services at speed up to 100 Gb/s.  
o	ITC has high-capacity water and sewer.
  
•  Scalability and Expansion Opportunities:  
o	The ITC campus offers ample room for scalability and expansion to accommodate a growing demand for computing resources.  With customizable floor plans and available land for future development, it provides data operators with the flexibility to scale their operations according to their needs.
  
•  Advanced Security Measures:  
o	Security is a top priority for the Cleveland Clinic.  The property is equipped with advanced security features.  The building offers fire protection and a sprinkler system.  
o	The building is located across the street from the Independence police and fire departments.
  
•  Environmental Sustainability:  
o	ITC is committed to environmental sustainability and energy efficiency.  It incorporates a solar panel farm on the rooftop and a geothermal HVAC system. 
o	LEED certified, Silver.  
o	Electric service can also be provided from Constellation Energy’s nuclear facility, which could offer carbon-free certification.
  
•  Data Center Tax Exemption:
o	Ohio provides a sales-tax exemption rate and term that allow for partial or full sales-tax exemption on the purchase of eligible data center equipment. Projects must meet minimum investment and payroll thresholds to be eligible. Final approval of the tax exemption is contingent upon the approval of the Ohio Tax Credit Authority.
ABOUT THE OWNER:
Cumberland will focus on the acquisition, revitalization, and management of existing commercial properties. The financial goal is to make long-term investments that generate positive cash flow.

They add value through creative design solutions, leveraging sustainable design and green technologies. Their approach aims to generate economic benefits for the company, property users, and the community as a whole. By integrating these principles effectively into their projects, they strive to enhance both environmental sustainability and societal well-being.

PROPERTY OVERVIEW:
The Wrigley Building is one of America's most famous office towers and an iconic symbol of Chicago. The Wrigley Building is located on Michigan Avenue along the north bank of the Chicago River, at the southernmost point of Chicago's Magnificent Mile. The building is a designated landmark consisting of two towers connected by two enclosed walkways on the 3rd and 14th floors. 
  
Zeller Development Corporation led the $70 million renovation of the 90-year-old building to a modernized office product with renovated lobbies, elevator cabs, multi-tenant corridors, restrooms, a conference center, a tenant lounge, and a health club. The renovation includes all new windows, HVAC, plumbing, electrical and sprinkler system. The redevelopment restored the intent of the original design and transformed the expansive plaza into a two-level, 50,000-square-foot dining and retail shopping destination.
  
Transportation includes Chicago Water Taxi dock at The Wrigley Building, with complimentary service to Ogilvie Transportation Center and Union Station. The water taxi is a 10-minute ride to the Metra train station. Additionally, CTA Express buses reach the Chicago Midway and O'Hare International Airports in less than 30 minutes. This vibrant downtown Magnificent Mile corridor is home to a plethora of restaurants, cocktail bars, pubs, shopping, and services. When a white-glove work experience, connectivity, and convenience are key, The Wrigley Building is the ideal work, live, play destination.

PROPERTY OVERVIEW:
Prime Retail Opportunity at 601 N. Wells St., River North, Chicago
Nestled in the heart of Chicago's dynamic and affluent River North district, the retail space at 601 N. Wells St. presents a rare leasing opportunity. This freestanding property, offering 2,800 square feet of versatile retail space, combines historic charm with modern amenities following a comprehensive renovation in 2020.
Location and Lifestyle
Strategically positioned at the crossroads of W. Ohio St. and N. Wells St., this property benefits from an impressive daily traffic count of 31,113 vehicles and is enveloped by an affluent demographic with an average household income of $142,393 within a 3-mile radius. River North is a cultural and lifestyle hub, known for its upscale dining, vibrant nightlife, and a community that values fitness, organic foods, and the arts. This makes 601 N. Wells St. an ideal location for businesses aiming to thrive in a lively urban environment.
Retail Space Features
- Size and Structure: A total of 2,800 SF available, with a flexible floor plan (2,000 SF on the 1st floor and 800 SF on the 2nd floor), allowing for a range of retail configurations.
- Economic and Demographic Strength: Surrounded by a dense, high-income population and significant consumer spending power ($7.9 billion within 3 miles).
- Zoning Flexibility: DX-5 zoning permits a variety of uses, from traditional retail to innovative service concepts, supporting a vibrant mix of commercial activities.
- Visibility and Accessibility: Exceptional visibility due to high traffic volumes, enhanced by excellent accessibility via public transportation, walking, and biking paths.
Connectivity and Community
River North is a testament to Chicago's ability to blend urban living with luxury. The neighborhood's proximity to the Magnificent Mile, bordered by the Chicago River, positions 601 N. Wells St. as a gateway to one of the city's most sought-after districts. This area is not just a place to do business but a place to become a part of Chicago's thriving community fabric.
A Unique Opportunity
This offering is more than just a retail space; it's a chance to be at the heart of Chicago's economic and cultural activity. Ideal for brands and businesses aiming to establish or expand their presence in a high-growth area, 601 N. Wells St. promises visibility, flexibility, and connectivity.
Seize the opportunity to make a mark in River North, where commerce meets community, and tradition meets innovation.

PROPERTY OVERVIEW:
Introducing an exceptional 17,800 square foot, four-story mixed-use commercial condo building ideally situated at the bustling intersection of Ontario Street, just east of the vibrant crossroads of State and Dearborn Streets. This magnificent property is nestled within Chicago's Central Business District and resides at the heart of the thriving River North neighborhood, offering four distinct units all ranging from approximately 3,500 SF-4,000 SF to cater to a range of business and residential needs.
Positioned on Ontario Street, a prominent thoroughfare connecting to the Kennedy and Dan Ryan Expressways, this property is a showcase of modern versatility. The first floor's Unit 100 is currently occupied and not available for lease, but Unit 200 on the second floor provides an ideal leasing opportunity, tailor-made for plastic surgeons, medical practitioners, or dentists.
Unit 300 on the third floor is artfully designed as a live/work space and is currently unavailable. Meanwhile, Unit 400 on the fourth floor is a luxurious residential apartment and is available for Lease.
Nestled within a bustling retail enclave, this property is surrounded by chic boutiques, world-class hotels, and trendy dining establishments such as Redhead Piano Bar, Gordon Ramsay Burger, Hard Rock Café, and TAO Chicago. It is further enhanced by the presence of popular retailers including Starbucks, Whole Foods, Lifetimes Fitness, and numerous others.
Accessibility is key, with convenient connections to CTA train and bus lines, as well as swift access to all major expressways. Multiple nearby public parking garages ensure easy parking solutions, while proximity to CTA bus lines enhances accessibility. The building itself features dual entrances and boasts a state-of-the-art ButterflyMX digital entry system, providing both security and technological sophistication.
This unique property is a prime opportunity to establish your business in a prestigious location, capitalize on the thriving local market, and enjoy the convenience of a well-connected urban setting in the heart of Chicago.

Name: The Sydni Building
PROPERTY OVERVIEW: Architectural Grandeur in Bronzeville with the musically historical Sydni Building. This iconic landmark was once home to the legendary 708 Blues Club, frequented by musical greats like Buddy Guy and Muddy Waters. This storied past with ties to iconic musicians make it a rare gem waiting for a new chapter. This space boasting over 7000 square feet of stunning timber post and beam construction feature a dramatic barrel-vaulted open bow truss ceiling. Ready for Your Vision: Extensive repairs and improvements have already been made, providing a blank canvas for your custom build-out. Enjoy the loft aesthetic with exposed sandblasted brick walls and a rebuilt concrete floor. Flexible B1-1 zoning, the possibilities are endless. Benefit from an included rear loading dock with an overhead door off the alley, average 12-foot ceiling heights, stairwell's and elevator shafts have also been rebuilt. Conveniently located in the heart of Bronzeville with shopping, transportation, restaurants, expressways and more all close by.

Name: 542 South Dearborn - The Pontiac Building
PROPERTY OVERVIEW:
Planned building renovations currently underway include the lobby, elevator cabs, select common corridors and new spec suites.
542 S. Dearborn St., also known as The Pontiac Building, was built in 1891 and is the oldest surviving building in downtown Chicago designed by architects Holabird & Roche. The building’s architectural significance landed it a place on the National Registry of Historic Places in 1976.
The Pontiac Building is located on Printers Row, an area that was developed in the late 19th century by printing and publishing firms that constructed facilities near the Dearborn Street railroad station. According to the city’s historic landmark website, the area’s unusual street pattern of long narrow blocks was constructed to provide the buildings an abundance of natural light, which was necessary for engraving and typesetting.
Potbelly's located on-site. Within 2 blocks of 3 different "L" stations and the LaSalle Metra Station.

The ceiling heights range from approximately 20 feet to 35 feet, and outdoor seating is permitted on the sidewalk. The black iron pathway is planned but not yet installed.
The zoning for The Arthur Harris Parcel is PD-1507, and the landlord is LG Development, a reputable developer with an excellent track record in the Chicago area. Retail delivery date is available now, with residential units also available now for renters.

PROPERTY OVERVIEW: The cafe space and commercial kitchen are situated on the first floor of the Axis Apartments and Lofts building on East Ontario Street between Michigan Avenue and Lake Shore Drive. Streeterville is a neighborhood in the Near North Side community area of Chicago, north of the Chicago River. It is bounded by the river on the south, the Magnificent Mile portion of Michigan Avenue on the west, and Lake Michigan on the north and east, according to most sources, although the City of Chicago only recognizes a small portion of this region as Streeterville. The tourist attraction of Navy Pier extends out into the lake from southern Streeterville. The area contains a combination of hotels, restaurants, professional office centers, residential high-rises, universities, medical facilities, and cultural venues. The area has undergone increased development in the early 21st century as numerous empty lots in Streeterville have been converted into commercial and residential properties, especially in the southern part of the neighborhood.

Name: Mutual Fire Ins. Co. Building
PROPERTY OVERVIEW:
The Mutual Building, one of Covington’s most prominent historic buildings located at ‘ground zero’ in Covington’s downtown urban center, is ideally located at the intersection of Madison Ave & Pike St. 
Built in 1921, the building originally housed the Covington Industrial Club (a precursor to the Chamber of Commerce), offices for the Mutual Insurance Company and numerous restaurants. 
After a long period of vacancy & declining condition, the City of Covington purchased the 30,000 square foot building in 2012 with the hopes of spurring redevelopment of the site.  In 2014, the building was fully restored with a significant investment to add 11,000 square feet of new retail & commercial space and 15 new market-rate apartments while preserving and enhancing the architectural character for the future.  
The building is ideally located in the heart of Covington across the street from the City Building, Hotel Covington and the new North development, along with close proximity to numerous bars, restaurants, and uniquely Covington retail establishments.

Located at the high point of Cincinnati, The District at Clifton Heights is a transformational, mixed-use development connecting campus and community. The District totals five acres in size along both sides of Straight Street, an ideal location that provides premium views in an active, pedestrian-oriented neighborhood. The urban development blends the fast-growing University of Cincinnati community with Cincy locals, bringing together a diverse mix of neighbors, students, employees and visitors by creating a destination to get away from it all, in the heart of it all.
As the largest private real estate investment in the history of Cincinnati, a development of this scale doesn’t come to life without a strong sense of community. With Trinitas’ proven expertise in university-centric development, and Crawford Hoying’s ongoing success in retail, hospitality and multifamily uses, The District of Clifton Heights will be home to an exciting blend of businesses, restaurants, housing options and more in a key area in the heart of Clifton Heights.

PROPERTY OVERVIEW:
Nestled between the historic buildings of Vine Street, on the corner of 15th Avenue, this modern entrepreneurial space invites professionals and creatives to take up the mantle of the artists and artisans that have called Over the Rhine home for the last 120 years. Within this location’s private offices, greenery-filled terraces, and wide-open meeting spaces, you can boost you and your company’s productivity in an environment designed to inspire.  Built to incorporate materials and structures from the surrounding neighborhood, this strikingly distinct location commands immediate attention. This is a workplace that adapts as you use it – a truly flexible workspace. Want to put your head down and get some work done? The super-fast Wi-Fi connection and variety of spaces means you’ll find the perfect nook for crunch-time cramming. Thirsty? Grab a latte at the in-house coffee bar, or head out to one of the independent cafes in the surrounding area. Then, slip home on the bus or train from the nearby stations, or take a walk through the heritage filled streets, passing parks and theaters as you go.
SPACES is ready for a new world of work with the implementation of hygiene and physical distancing measures recommended by local governments and the World Health Organisation (WHO). SPACES has increased the cleaning frequency, focusing on high touchpoint areas, surfaces, and workspaces. SPACES has taken the principles of physical distancing and adapted them for the workplace with reconfigured workspaces and clear information, signage, and protocols to ensure minimal person-to-person contact. SPACES has established a meeting room safety protocol that encompasses the use of spaced seating, moving around clockwise, and maintaining a safe distance for catering.

PROPERTY OVERVIEW: The premier office, hotel, and restaurant center in Northern Kentucky, RiverCenter has transformed the way the Greater Cincinnati area does business. The complex has earned a prestigious reputation for unparalleled convenience, elegance, cost efficiency, and quality service for Tri-State business leaders. The tallest of the three towers, RiverCenter I is distinguished by its dramatic, panoramic views of the downtown Cincinnati skyline and the Ohio River. Touting 19 stories of Class A office space, the building offers prestige, a central location, and convenience for corporate headquarters and growing companies to exploit. Businesses enjoy exclusive access to a state-of-the-art fitness center and the 75-seat RiverCenter media center in addition to the nearby 110,000 square-foot Northern Kentucky Convention Center and two hotels totaling 547 rooms. Perhaps most impressive of all, Corporex’s in-house tenant finish department offers architecture, design, and construction management that can take any floor from a blank canvas to the ideal creative space for a company. RiverCenter is in the heart of this bustling area without the hassles of downtown Cincinnati traffic congestion. There are 3,200 parking spots available in the immediate area for auto commuters. For public transportation, there is an on-site Cincinnati Red Bike station, the Southbank Shuttle Trolley offers service every 15 minutes to downtown Cincinnati, Covington, Newport, and Bellevue, and Transit Authority of Northern Kentucky (TANK) provides services to Boone, Campbell, and Kenton Counties. It is also just a 24-minute drive to the Cincinnati/Northern Kentucky International Airport (CVG). In addition to the on-site dining options such as FIRE, Butler’s Pantry, and Biscuits Burgers, there are two dozen neighborhood restaurants within walking distance. Employers and employees are looking for the “it” factor when it comes to office space, and RiverCenter checks all those boxes. The walkability of the community and the amenities of RiverCenter make it the premier destination to live, work, and play.

PROPERTY OVERVIEW: Calling all creatives!! Don't miss your chance to be a part of The Historic Brownhoist. This incredible building was built and has been in operation since 1880 and has a distinct sense of history in every corner, including the oldest operating elevator in Cleveland! The Brownhoist is looking for tenants of all kinds, especially creatives who are doing unique and noteworthy things. If you are looking for office space in a unique venue in a building that is fostering a sense of community, you need to check this out and see if it's a good fit. Rent includes all utilities, even Wifi! There is a main floor receptionist available M-F 9:30 - 4 pm and you can have your mail sent to the building. Multiple common areas are also available in the building that can be used to relax, have group sessions or just get a change of scenery when they are not reserved. A gorgeous, completely original boardroom is on the first floor and a grand ballroom is on the second floor. Don't miss the basement Geekeasy (video games and pinball) or the library / game room, located in a vault (one of 7 on the property). Contact listing agent for showing information. This space is perfect for an artist or small business owner who is looking for a smaller space but wants to be part of a bigger community. The third floor location is peaceful and tenants have access to all the common areas and amenities available.
